&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stroke Medicine Consultant salary range £79,860 - £107,668&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AAC Panel date:&lt;/strong&gt; TBC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Realising your potential with Mid Essex Hospitals&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is one of a number of opportunities within our hospitals and our partner hospitals as we transition into a ‘Group’ hospital model. Our focus is around expanding our services, to serve our thriving and vibrant community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You may wish to further develop your clinical career with a specialist interest, or aspire to be a Clinical Leader or Educator to lead innovative services, and expand the training we offer to our trainees into the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our trainees, are appointed through the new Chelmsford based Anglia Ruskin Medical School, and consistently rate their training experience with us as being excellent to very good.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To explore what could be available to you to advance your potential within this role, or to arrange an informal social visit to enjoy our location and to meet our dedicated, professional and diverse colleagues. Interested applicants are invited in the first instance to contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Kirthivasan, email Ramanathan.Kirthivasan@meht.nhs.uk (Stroke Lead) telephone 01245 513714; Dr Matt Sweeting, email matthew.sweeting@meht.nhs.uk , Divisional Director for Medicine and Emergency Services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location, with a relocation policy package&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chelmsford is set within picturesque ‘Constable’ countryside. With a variety of places to explore, sites to see, plenty of shopping experiences, great restaurants and theatre, as well as the home to ‘Essex cricket club’ there really is something for everyone!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2018, the ‘Times’ voted Chelmsford as best place to live in the UK, regional winner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our hospital has an outstanding nursery. We are spoilt for choice with excellent schools, housing and transport links. Central London is a 25 minute train ride, Stansted airport 30 minutes away, and the beach 20 miles away.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Further information on our location can be found via the Visit Essex website.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Dr. Ramanathan Kirthivasan - Lead Stroke Consultant and Clinical Director on ramanathan.kirthivasan@meht.nhs.uk &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Dr Matt Sweeting - Divisional Director on matthew.sweeting@meht.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
